article.headline: Princeton 76, Florida A&amp,M 61
article.story: TALLAHASSEE, Fla. -- Douglas Davis had 18 points to lead four double-figure scorers for Princeton in a 76-61 win over Florida A&M Sunday, wrapping up the two-game Florida portion of the Tigers' season-high seven-game road trip. Ian Hummer added 15 points, T.J. Bray had 14 and Denton Koon 13 for the Tigers (8-7), whose win wraps up an undefeated record in the team's only trip to the Sunshine State during the regular season. The highlight of the swing came on Friday when Princeton was across town for a 75-73 triple-overtime win at Florida State. Princeton led by as many as 13 points in the first half, 40-30 at the intermission and by 20 at one juncture after the break in downing FAMU. The Tigers have now won seven of their last nine after a 1-5 start, while the Rattlers (2-12) have lost five straight. Reggie Lewis led FAMU with 19 points.
